headline: A lawsuit involving Kroger and singer Jewel could shed light on why the former supermarket CEO mysteriously resigned
summary: In March, Kroger’s CEO resigned from his corner-office role after nearly five decades at the company — an abrupt exit that left questions and $11 million on the table. Now, a lawsuit involving ’90s folk sensation Jewel could bring some answers.

headline: Yerba Madre's "Watermelody" Marks First Seasonal Flavor, First Yellow Can Under New Name
summary: Yerba Madre – formerly known as Guayakí Yerba Mate – is ushering in a bold new era of innovation with the launch of Watermelody, the first seasonal release to debut under its new name and refreshed iconic yellow can design.
